  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: 1.3.5\nOS & Version: OSX\n#### Expected behaviour\n\nIf I run `geth --exec \"invalid()\" attach ipc://.../geth.ipc` it should exit with a non-zero error code.\n#### Actual behaviour\n\nIt exits with error code 0 (even though the above command is clearly invalid) and the error message returned in `stdout` rather than `stderr`:\n\n``` bash\n$ geth --exec \"invalid()\" attach ipc:///var/folders/4v/br6x6mlx113235v1lz39nwfc0000gn/T/tmp-74391lqz0pEtM1uNl/geth.ipc\nerror: ReferenceError: 'invalid' is not defined\n$ echo $?\n0\n```\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\nRun `geth --exec \"invalid()\" attach ipc://.../geth.ipc`  (replace `ipc..` with valid path)\n",
